<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="504" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[813,1456,1763,2026]" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">
HABITATS AND DISTRIBUTION. — This lowland species is found throughout much of West Africa, as well as along the Nile River from 
<collectingCountry box="[813,874,1816,1840]" name="Sudan" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Sudan</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[905,985,1816,1840]" name="Uganda" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Uganda</collectingCountry>
. It has also been recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1342,1816,1840]" name="Uganda" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1351,1413,1817,1841]" name="Kenya" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[813,897,1843,1867]" name="Tanzania" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[908,1057,1843,1867]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" pagination="516 - 518" refId="ref26313" refString="HAPPOLD M. 2013 g. - Tadarida major Lappet-eared Free-tailed Bat, in M. HAPPOLD &amp; D. C. D. HaPPOLD (eds). The Mammals of Africa. Vol. IV. Hegdehogs, shrews and bats. Bloomsbury Publishing, London: 516 - 518. http: // doi. org / 10.5040 / 9781472926944.0280" type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="g">
Happold 
<quantity box="[997,1057,1843,1867]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.013" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" unit="g" value="2013.0">2013g</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1223,1843,1867]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[1083,1223,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Tadarida major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[1266,1361,1843,1866]" name="Cameroon" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, the species has been recorded previously in the Sahelian zone of northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1360,1455,1870,1893]" name="Cameroon" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bakwo Fils" box="[821,1042,1896,1920]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Bakwo Fils" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" pagination="16 - 22" refId="ref23656" refString="BAKWO FILS E. M., BOL A. G., TSALA B. D., GUIKE B. B., DAVID EMERY T. &amp; FOTSO KUATE A. 2014. - Diversity of bats of the Far North Region of Cameroon with two first records for the country. Biodiversity 15: 16 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 1488 8386.2014. 889578" type="journal article" year="2014">Bakwo Fils et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[1042,1050,1896,1919]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">)</emphasis>
The species primarily inhabits savannahs but has also been recorded in rainforest habitats where it roosts in hollow trees and holes in walls of buildings (
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[1243,1399,1949,1973]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" pagination="516 - 518" refId="ref26313" refString="HAPPOLD M. 2013 g. - Tadarida major Lappet-eared Free-tailed Bat, in M. HAPPOLD &amp; D. C. D. HaPPOLD (eds). The Mammals of Africa. Vol. IV. Hegdehogs, shrews and bats. Bloomsbury Publishing, London: 516 - 518. http: // doi. org / 10.5040 / 9781472926944.0280" type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="g">
Happold 
<quantity box="[1336,1399,1949,1973]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.013" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" unit="g" value="2013.0">2013g</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is threatened in some part of its range by habitat loss and disturbance of old building (
<bibRefCitation author="Monadjem" box="[973,1203,2001,2026]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Monadjem" pageId="23" pageNumber="504" pagination="22018874" refId="ref28064" refString="MONADJEM A., COTTERILL F., HUTSON A. M., MICKLEBURGH S. &amp; BERGMANS W. 2017 b. - Chaerephon major. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e. T 4314 A 22018874. https: // doi. org / 10.2305 / IUCN. UK. 2017 - 2. RLTS. T 4314 A 22018874. en" type="journal article" year="2017" yearSuffix="b">
Monadjem 
<emphasis box="[1087,1134,2001,2025]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="504">et al.</emphasis>
2017b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
